Section 1:
SR 35 Text skip navigation SENATE PRESIDENT SENATORS COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS SENATE CLERK SENATE RULES HOUSE SPEAKER DELEGATES COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS HOUSE CLERK HOUSE RULES HOUSE STAFF JOINT INTERIM COMMITTEES LEGISLATIVE ADMINISTRATOR LEGISLATIVE SERVICES DIVISION PUBLIC INFORMATION LEGISLATIVE AUTOMATED SYSTEMS DIVISION LEGISLATIVE AUDITOR'S OFFICE PERFORMANCE EVALUATION & RESEARCH DIVISION POST AUDIT DIVISION BUDGET DIVISION REGULATORY AND FISCAL AFFAIRS DIVISION CLAIMS COMMISSION CRIME VICTIMS RULE-MAKING REVIEW SPECIAL INVESTIGATIONS JUDICIAL COMP. COMMISSION JOINT RULES STAFF INFO BILL STATUS BILL STATUS BILL TRACKING STATE LAW WEST VIRGINIA CODE ACTS OF THE LEGISLATURE CODE OF 1931 WV CONSTITUTION US CONSTITUTION REPORTS AGENCY REPORTS AGENCY GRANT AWARDS PERFORMANCE EVALUATIONS POST AUDITS EDUCATIONAL CITIZEN’S GUIDE INTERNSHIP PROGRAM PAGE PROGRAM PUBLICATIONS PHOTO GALLERY CAPITOL HISTORY HOW A BILL BECOMES LAW CONTACT SENATE ROSTER HOUSE ROSTER PUBLIC INFO. NEWS RELEASES HELPFUL LINKS Introduced Version Senate Resolution 35 History |  Email Key: Green = existing Code. Red = new code to be enacted SENATE RESOLUTION 35(By Senators Rucker, Rose, Chapman, and Helton)[Introduced March 18, 2025] Recognizing the West Virginia Mothers and Babies Support Program for their outstanding achievements.Whereas, The West Virginia Mothers and Babies Support Program (WVMBSP) has had an extraordinary impact during the 2023-2024 program year, successfully expanding services to women and babies in all 55 counties across the state; andWhereas, The program has enabled 49 Pregnancy Help Organization (PHO) locations, including 23 pregnancy care centers, three maternity homes, and 23 social service agencies to provide critical assistance, resulting in 11,858 women and babies receiving life-affirming support; andWhereas, The WVMBSP facilitated major expansions, such as Choices Women’s Center in Clarksburg moving to a larger facility to offer more services, and Compass Women’s Center in Morgantown acquiring an ultrasound machine to transition into a medical clinic providing free ultrasounds to women in need; andWhereas, The program funded essential resources, including car seats, cribs, prenatal vitamins, hygiene supplies, parenting education, and over 150,000 diapers to support families in need; andWhereas, The monthly Mountaineer Legal Seminars, led by esteemed legal expert Jeanneane Maxon, provided PHOs with crucial education on legal compliance, child abuse reporting, client confidentiality, and policy best practices, equipping centers to better serve mothers and babies; andWhereas, The Fatherhood Programs encouraged increased paternal involvement, offering mentorship, parenting education, and community support to fathers, thereby strengthening families; andWhereas, WVMBSP’s commitment to excellence included 23 in-person and 3 virtual site visits to ensure compliance, program effectiveness, and the highest standard of care for families; andWhereas, The program received overwhelmingly positive feedback, with PHOs reporting that funding allowed them to significantly expand services, and clients expressing deep gratitude for the life-changing support they received, as reflected in testimonials such as: “This program has been an absolute blessing. I would not have been able to provide for my baby without the help we received.” and “The financial support for our center allowed us to dream big and serve more women than we ever imagined.”; therefore, be itResolved by the Senate:That the Senate hereby recognizes the West Virginia Mothers and Babies Support Program for their outstanding achievements; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Senate acknowledge the dedication of the WVPCC team, PHOs, and community partners who have worked tirelessly to make this program a success, ensuring that West Virginia remains a place where mothers and babies receive the care, support, and dignity they deserve; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Clerk is hereby directed to forward a copy of this resolution to the West Virginia Mothers and Babies Support Program team. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone:


