s, and Compass Women’s Center in Morgantown acquiring an ultrasound machine to transition into a medical clinic providing free ultrasounds to women in need; andWhereas, The program funded essential resources, including car seats, cribs, prenatal vitamins, hygiene supplies, parenting education, and over 150,000 diapers to support families in need; andWhereas, The monthly Mountaineer Legal Seminars, led by esteemed legal expert Jeanneane Maxon, provided PHOs with crucial education on legal compliance, child abuse reporting, client confidentiality, and policy best practices, equipping centers to better serve mothers and babies; andWhereas, The Fatherhood Programs encouraged increased paternal involvement, offering mentorship, parenting education, and community support to fathers, thereby strengthening families; andWhereas, WVMBSP’s commitment to excellence included 23 in-person and 3 virtual site visits to ensure compliance, program effectiveness, and the highest standard of care for families; andWhereas, The program received overwhelmingly positive feedback, with PHOs reporting that funding allowed them to significantly expand services, and clients expressing deep gratitude for the life-changing support they received, as reflected in testimonials such as: “This program has been an absolute blessing. I would not have been able to provide for my baby without the help we received.” and “The financial support for our center allowed us to dream big and serve more women than we ever imagined.”; therefore, be itResolved by the Senate:That the Senate hereby recognizes the West Virginia Mothers and Babies Support Program for their outstanding achievements; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Senate acknowledge the dedication of the WVPCC team, PHOs, and community partners who have worked tirelessly to make this program a success, ensuring that West Virginia remains a place where mothers and babies receive the care, support, and dignity they deserve; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Clerk is hereby directed to forward a copy of this resolution to the West Virginia Mothers and Babies Support Program team. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone: